description: The Jajangmyeon Museum is a South Korean museum with Jajangmyeon as its main body. The museum was formerly a Chinese restaurant built in 1908 called Gonghechun. Here, tourists can learn about the history of overseas Chinese in Korea and the changes in modern social life through the introduction of Jajangmyeon. The ground floor of the museum is the restoration of the kitchen of the year, and the second floor is the restoration of several restaurants of the year. All the exhibition panels have Chinese descriptions.
